Containerization(modern approach):
----------------------------------
    Idea: package everything together -> run anywhere

    what is container:
    ------------------
    A container = Application + dependencies + configs + environment

        real-life example:
        ------------------
        Like a tiffin box,
        - food inside = your app
        - box = container
        - carry anywhere = works same

    How it works:
    -------------
    Hardware -> OS -> Docker -> Containers

        * no separate OS per container
        * all containers share same OS
        * each container has its own process space
        * each container has its own file system
        * each container has its own network space

    Key Difference:
    ---------------
     > Virtual Machine:
       VM = App + OS

     > Container:
       App only (uses host OS)

    Why containers are better:
    -------------------------
    Light weight:
        - no os inside container
        - uses less memory
    Fast:
        - starts in seconds
        - vm takes minutes

    Portable: build once, run anywhere
        works same in:
            - laptop
            - dev
            - qa
            - production

    No works on my machine issue:
    -----------------------------
    because: dependencies are inside container

    Better resource usage:
    ----------------------
    Containers share CPU/RAM dynamically

    * Isolation:
    -------------
    Even though containers share same OS:
    they are isolating using:
        Namespaces - separate spaces
        cgroups - resource control

    simple understanding:
    ---------------------
    - same house
    - different rooms
    - everyone independent


    | Feature        | Virtual Machine | Container      |
    | -------------- | --------------- | -------------- |
    | OS             | Each VM has OS  | No OS (shared) |
    | Size           | Large (GBs)     | Small (MBs)    |
    | Speed          | Slow            | Fast           |
    | Resource usage | High            | Low            |
    | Startup        | Minutes         | Seconds        |
    | Isolation      | Hardware level  | OS level       |


    AWS Example:
    ------------
    - EC2 instance = virtual machine
      NOT container
      if your install docker inside EC2 - then containers

    Final Simple Understanding:
    ---------------------------
    Old:
        one server + one app  --> waste resources

    VM:
        one server + multiple vms --> better but heavy

    container:
        one server --> multiple containers -> fast, lightweight, portable





























